# next()

**Instance Method**

Returns the next dictionary in the sequence.

## Declaration

```swift
func next() async throws -> WAPairedDevice.DevicesSequence.AsyncIterator.Element?
```

## Return Value

The next [doc://com.apple.wifiaware/documentation/WiFiAware/WAPairedDevice/Devices] snapshot, or `nil` if it’s at the end of the sequence.

## Discussion

The [doc://com.apple.wifiaware/documentation/WiFiAware/WAPairedDevice/Devices] dictionary holds the latest snapshot of the currently paired devices that are known and accessible to your app.



## Getting the next asynchronous update

- **WAPairedDevice.DevicesSequence.AsyncIterator.Element**: A dictionary holding a snapshot of currently paired devices accessible to your app.
